#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an5.161"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.161:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:0.2"
msgid "17. Āghātavagga "
msgstr "17. Resentment "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.161:0.3"
msgid "161. Paṭhamaāghātapaṭivinayasutta "
msgstr "161. Getting Rid of Resentment (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.186, sc1
msgctxt "an5.161:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, āghātapaṭivinayā yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso paṭivinetabbo. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone. "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.2"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:1.3"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, mettā tasmiṃ puggale bhāvetabbā; "
msgstr "You should develop love for a person you resent. "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.4"
msgid "evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. "
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:1.5"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, karuṇā tasmiṃ puggale bhāvetabbā; "
msgstr "You should develop compassion for a person you resent. … "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.6"
msgid "evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:1.7"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, upekkhā tasmiṃ puggale bhāvetabbā; "
msgstr "You should develop equanimity for a person you resent. … "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.8"
msgid "evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:1.9"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, asatiamanasikāro tasmiṃ puggale āpajjitabbo; "
msgstr "You should disregard a person you resent, paying no attention to them. … "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.10"
msgid "evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:1.11"
msgid "Yasmiṃ, bhikkhave, puggale āghāto jāyetha, kammassakatā tasmiṃ puggale adhiṭṭhātabbā: "
msgstr "You should apply the concept that we are the owners of our deeds to that person: "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.12"
msgid "‘kammassako ayamāyasmā kammadāyādo kammayoni kammabandhu kammapaṭisaraṇo, "
msgstr "‘This venerable is the owner of their deeds and heir to their deeds. Deeds are their womb, their relative, and their refuge. "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.13"
msgid "yaṃ kammaṃ karissati kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā tassa dāyādo bhavissatī’ti; "
msgstr "They shall be the heir of whatever deeds they do, whether good or bad.’ "

msgctxt "an5.161:1.14"
msgid "evaṃ tasmiṃ puggale āghāto paṭivinetabbo. "
msgstr "That’s how to get rid of resentment for that person. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.161:1.15"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, pañca āghātapaṭivinayā, yattha bhikkhuno uppanno āghāto sabbaso paṭivinetabbo”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant should use these five methods to completely get rid of resentment when it has arisen toward anyone.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.161:1.16"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

